title: Lionel Hampton's 90th birthday
description: 5 x 7 inch photograph. Lionel Hampton on vibraphone and Bill Clinton on saxophone in the East Room of the White House celebrating Hampton's 90th birthday. Washington D.C.  Inscription on back reads "July 23, 1998 in the East Room of the White House-Washington, DC  The President and Mrs. Clinton invited Lionel Hampton to be their guest at the White house, along with his band, to celebrate his 90th birthday (actually April 20) and to honor him for his vast[?] contributions to jazz during his lifetime.  150 invited guests attended.  Lionel's Band was introduced by Hillary Clinton along with an eloquent speech by her about Lionel's musical gifts to the world & how important jazz was as an American Ambassador.  The Band [?] many numbers to tumultuous applause & then President Clinton accepted Lionel's invitation to play &[?] [?] with a beautiful rendition of 'My Funny Valentine'"
